snippet.textDisplay: I love cold pizza, but some pizza's are better cold than others.  I love cold pizza for breakfast.  For lunch or dinner I will usually reheat.  My preferred method of reheating only works with a gas oven, but I will put the pizza in a cold oven and turn the oven on to 435.  Something about the process of preheating makes the pizza perfect, arguably better than it was fresh.  I wait for the oven to beep, and if I can smell the pizza, it's done, if not, I give it a couple more mins.  You're welcome.
